{{ 'ka-nav.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{%- comment -%}
  is_about_us — Docs/about-us-build-spec.md Section 6 (H3). Drives the
  new .is-current state on the mobile drawer's About link (and the
  matching link in ka-footer.liquid). Written as a small reusable check
  (not a one-off hardcoded string comparison inline) so it can be
  extended the same way for Collection/Product/Cart's own nav links
  later, per the spec's own flagged follow-up — not done here since
  that is out of this page's scope.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign is_about_us = false -%}
{%- if request.page_type == 'page' and page.handle == 'about-us' -%}{%- assign is_about_us = true -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- comment -%}
  ka-collection-grid.css lives here (not just in sections/ka-collection-grid.liquid)
  because .ka-p-card is now a genuinely sitewide component, not a Collection-page-only
  one: the search overlay (below) and templates/search.json both reuse it verbatim,
  and ka-nav.liquid renders on every template. sections/ka-collection-grid.liquid keeps
  its own stylesheet_tag too (harmless duplicate <link> only on Collection pages,
  browsers dedupe the fetch) rather than removing it and creating a hidden cross-file
  dependency that would break the Collection page if this file's load order ever changed.
{%- endcomment -%}
{{ 'ka-collection-grid.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{{ 'ka-search.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'ka-search.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

{%- comment -%}
  Global header: utility bar (z-index 101, top:0, permanent) + nav (z-index 100, top:34px).
  Homepage opens transparent over the dark hero and crystallises on scroll (.scrolled added
  by ka-theme.js). Collection / Product / all other templates have no dark hero behind the
  nav, so they render permanently in the settled (opaque/blurred) state via .ka-nav--settled
  and need no scroll listener. The nav NEVER changes `top` on scroll (utility bar overlap fix).

  Search — Docs/search-404-footer-build-spec.md Section 1. Trigger icon lives here in
  .ka-nav__actions (peer to the bag icon), NOT the utility bar (spec §1.2: would crowd
  the Task 86 currency chip and mix two different jobs in one strip). The overlay itself
  is rendered once, inline, near the bottom of this file (snippets/ka-search-overlay.liquid)
  — same pattern already used here for the mobile nav drawer and the shared currency menu,
  rather than a separate section requiring duplication across every template's settings.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign is_home = false -%}
{%- if request.page_type == 'index' -%}{%- assign is_home = true -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Utility bar — Round 3 fix (R3-3): the three phrases are wrapped in a
  ".ka-utility-bar__track" containing two identical ".ka-utility-bar__group"
  copies (the second copy is aria-hidden, purely decorative). Desktop is
  untouched (track just sits still). At the mobile breakpoint (<=900px,
  see ka-nav.css) the track animates translateX(0) -> translateX(-50%) in
  a continuous loop instead of wrapping to two lines. prefers-reduced-motion
  disables the animation and falls back to plain horizontal scroll (the
  duplicate group is hidden so it doesn't sit there inert).
  Spec: Docs/cta-architecture-revision.md Round 3 / R3-3.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="ka-utility-bar" role="complementary" aria-label="Service messages">
  {%- if settings.enable_currency_converter -%}<div class="ka-utility-bar__spacer" aria-hidden="true"></div>{%- endif -%}
  <div class="ka-utility-bar__track-wrap">
    <div class="ka-utility-bar__track">
      <span class="ka-utility-bar__group">
        <b>{{ section.settings.utility_1 }}</b><span aria-hidden="true">·</span><b>{{ section.settings.utility_2 }}</b><span aria-hidden="true">·</span><b>{{ section.settings.utility_3 }}</b>
      </span>
      <span class="ka-utility-bar__group" aria-hidden="true">
        <b>{{ section.settings.utility_1 }}</b><span aria-hidden="true">·</span><b>{{ section.settings.utility_2 }}</b><span aria-hidden="true">·</span><b>{{ section.settings.utility_3 }}</b>
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>
  {%- if settings.enable_currency_converter -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      Currency chip (Task 86) — the single, permanent, always-visible
      indicator of the active currency and the primary way to change
      it. Symbol + ISO code only, no flag, no country name (spec
      Section 2.1 + CD Note 2). Opens the shared menu below (2.3).
      Label starts as "₹ INR" server-side so JS-disabled visitors see
      a correct, sensible default; ka-currency.js overwrites it on load.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="ka-currency-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <button
      type="button"
      class="ka-currency-chip"
      id="ka-currency-chip"
      aria-haspopup="listbox"
      aria-expanded="false"
      aria-controls="ka-currency-menu"
    >
      <span class="ka-currency-chip__label" data-ka-currency-chip-label>₹ INR</span>
      <span class="ka-currency-chip__caret" aria-hidden="true">&#9662;</span>
    </button>
  {%- endif -%}
</div>

<nav class="ka-nav{% unless is_home %} ka-nav--settled{% endunless %}" id="ka-nav" role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">
  {%- comment -%}
    Toggle moved OUT of .ka-nav__actions and given its own grid-column:1
    position (revision v2, spec §1.2/§1.4) — mobile only (display:none at
    desktop, where .ka-nav__links occupies column 1 instead; the two are
    mutually exclusive per breakpoint, never simultaneously in the
    layout, so no grid conflict). It's also first in DOM order now, ahead
    of .ka-nav__links, so mobile tab order reads hamburger -> logo ->
    search -> bag, matching the new left-to-right visual order (spec §1.5).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <button class="ka-nav__toggle" id="ka-nav-toggle" aria-label="Open menu" aria-expanded="false">
    <span></span><span></span><span></span>
  </button>
  <ul class="ka-nav__links">
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_bestsellers }}">{{ section.settings.label_bestsellers }}</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_collections }}"{% if template contains 'collection' %} class="is-active"{% endif %}>{{ section.settings.label_collections }}</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_diaries }}">{{ section.settings.label_diaries }}</a></li>
  </ul>

  <a href="/" class="ka-nav__logo">{{ section.settings.logo_text }}<small>{{ section.settings.logo_subline }}</small></a>

  <div class="ka-nav__actions">
    {%- comment -%}
      Search trigger — Docs/search-404-footer-build-spec.md §1.2. Shares
      the bag icon's exact stroke spec (24x24 viewBox, stroke-width:1.4,
      round caps) via the common .ka-nav__icon-btn class, immediately
      left of the bag icon on every template.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <button
      type="button"
      class="ka-nav__icon-btn"
      id="ka-search-trigger"
      aria-label="Search"
      aria-haspopup="dialog"
      aria-controls="ka-search-overlay"
      aria-expanded="false"
    >
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="10.5" cy="10.5" r="6.5"/><path d="M20 20l-4.8-4.8"/></svg>
    </button>
    {%- comment -%}
      Bag icon — Round 2 addition (R2-7). Lives in every template via
      this shared section. Count badge is updated sitewide by
      window.kaUpdateBagCount() in ka-theme.js, which targets every
      [data-ka-bag-count] node (this one + the mobile drawer's). The
      data-count="0" attribute pairs with ka-nav.css's
      [data-count="0"] { display:none } so an empty bag shows no badge.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <a href="{{ routes.cart_url }}" class="ka-nav__icon-btn ka-nav__bag" aria-label="View your bag">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 8h12l-1 12H7L6 8z"/><path d="M9 8V6a3 3 0 0 1 6 0v2"/></svg>
      <span class="ka-nav__bag__count" data-ka-bag-count data-count="{{ cart.item_count }}">{% if cart.item_count > 0 %}{{ cart.item_count }}{% endif %}</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</nav>

<nav class="ka-mobile-nav" id="ka-mobile-nav" aria-hidden="true" aria-label="Mobile navigation">
  <button class="ka-mobile-nav__close" id="ka-nav-close" aria-label="Close menu">Close</button>
  <ul class="ka-mobile-nav__links">
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_bestsellers }}">{{ section.settings.label_bestsellers }}</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_collections }}">{{ section.settings.label_collections }}</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_diaries }}">{{ section.settings.label_diaries }}</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ section.settings.link_about }}"{% if is_about_us %} class="is-current"{% endif %}>About</a></li>
    <li><a href="#" data-ka-appt-link>Book an Appointment</a></li>
  </ul>
  {%- comment -%}
    My Bag row — Round 2 addition (R2-7), mobile-drawer equivalent of
    the desktop .ka-nav__bag icon. Same [data-ka-bag-count] contract.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <a href="{{ routes.cart_url }}" class="ka-mobile-nav__bag-row">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 8h12l-1 12H7L6 8z"/><path d="M9 8V6a3 3 0 0 1 6 0v2"/></svg>
    My Bag
    <span class="ka-mobile-nav__bag-count" data-ka-bag-count data-count="{{ cart.item_count }}">{% if cart.item_count > 0 %}{{ cart.item_count }}{% endif %}</span>
  </a>
  {%- if settings.enable_currency_converter -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      Currency row (Task 86, Section 2.2) — the drawer (z-index 200)
      renders above the utility bar (z-index 101), so the chip above
      is physically hidden while the drawer is open. This row is the
      same control, relocated so it's reachable here — sibling of the
      "My Bag" row, above the Concierge footer, same list-row language.
      Opens the identical shared menu below (2.3) — one source of truth.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <button
      type="button"
      class="ka-mobile-nav__currency-row"
      id="ka-currency-chip-mobile"
      aria-haspopup="listbox"
      aria-expanded="false"
      aria-controls="ka-currency-menu"
    >
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg>
      Currency
      <span class="val"><span data-ka-currency-chip-label>₹ INR</span><span class="ka-currency-chip__caret" aria-hidden="true">&#9662;</span></span>
    </button>
  {%- endif -%}
  <div class="ka-mobile-nav__footer">
    <p>Concierge</p>
    <a href="https://wa.me/{{ settings.whatsapp_number }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      {{ settings.whatsapp_display }}
    </a>
  </div>
</nav>

{%- comment -%}
  Search overlay (Docs/search-404-footer-build-spec.md Section 1) —
  rendered once here, same reasoning as the currency menu below: this
  section renders exactly once per page (no section-group duplication
  across templates), so one shared DOM node is correct. `section` is
  passed explicitly since snippets don't inherit it automatically —
  the overlay's popular-search chips/tiles read their labels, URLs and
  images straight from this section's own schema settings below.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- render 'ka-search-overlay', section: section -%}

{%- if settings.enable_currency_converter -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    Shared currency menu (Task 86, Section 2.3) — one DOM element,
    two presentations depending on viewport (dropdown >900px, bottom
    sheet <=900px, see ka-currency.css). Reachable from both the
    utility-bar chip and the mobile-drawer row above. Rendered once
    here since ka-nav.liquid renders exactly once per page (no
    section-group duplication across templates). List rows are built
    client-side by ka-currency.js so the active-state dot always
    reflects real detected/overridden state, never a guessed default.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="ka-currency-scrim" id="ka-currency-scrim"></div>
  <div class="ka-currency-menu" id="ka-currency-menu" role="listbox" aria-label="Select display currency" aria-hidden="true">
    <button type="button" class="ka-currency-menu__close" id="ka-currency-menu-close">Close</button>
    <div class="ka-currency-menu__handle" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="eyebrow ka-currency-menu__eyebrow">Currency</div>
    <ul class="ka-currency-menu__list" id="ka-currency-menu-list"></ul>
    <p class="ka-currency-menu__note">Prices shown for your convenience. Checkout completes in Indian Rupees.</p>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}

<script>
  /* "Book an Appointment" — TEMPORARY interim routing, same pattern as
     the Product page's openAppt(): until a real booking flow/calendar
     exists, every [data-ka-appt-link] click anywhere on the site opens
     the WhatsApp concierge thread instead. This single delegated
     listener (document-level) covers every page that includes ka-nav,
     so it handles the mobile drawer link here AND any other section
     that marks an element data-ka-appt-link (Product page CTA stack,
     Appointment section, Hero secondary CTA, Collection concierge band,
     Footer "Book an Appointment" link, etc. — see
     Docs/cta-architecture-revision.md Round 2, R2-4, and the soft-launch
     appointments-page-fix notes). Number comes from the theme's global
     settings.whatsapp_number (Theme Settings -> Contact), rendered
     server-side here since this is a .liquid file, not hardcoded.
     An optional data-ka-appt-text attribute lets a given link pre-fill a
     more specific enquiry message (e.g. "in-store" vs. "virtual" on the
     Appointment section); links without it just open WhatsApp with no
     pre-filled text, same as before this attribute existed.
     Flagged — do not let this silently become permanent. Re-wire every
     data-ka-appt-link element to a real booking flow URL once one exists. */
  document.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
    var link = e.target.closest && e.target.closest('[data-ka-appt-link]');
    if (!link) return;
    e.preventDefault();
    var waUrl = 'https://wa.me/{{ settings.whatsapp_number }}';
    var apptText = link.getAttribute('data-ka-appt-text');
    if (apptText) { waUrl += '?text=' + encodeURIComponent(apptText); }
    window.open(waUrl, '_blank');
  });
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Navigation",
  "tag": "header",
  "class": "ka-nav-section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Utility bar"
    },
    { "type": "text", "id": "utility_1", "label": "Utility phrase 1", "default": "Complimentary Worldwide Delivery" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "utility_2", "label": "Utility phrase 2", "default": "Hand-Embroidered to Order" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "utility_3", "label": "Utility phrase 3", "default": "Private & Virtual Appointments" },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Logo"
    },
    { "type": "text", "id": "logo_text",    "label": "Logo wordmark", "default": "Karishma Ashita" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "logo_subline", "label": "Logo sub-line", "default": "Bridal Couture · Mumbai" },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Desktop nav links"
    },
    { "type": "text", "id": "label_bestsellers", "label": "Signature label", "default": "Signature" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "link_bestsellers",  "label": "Signature URL" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "label_collections", "label": "Collections label", "default": "Collections" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "link_collections",  "label": "Collections URL" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "label_diaries", "label": "Client Diaries label", "default": "Client Diaries" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "link_diaries",  "label": "Client Diaries URL" },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Mobile nav additional links"
    },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "link_about",       "label": "About page URL" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "link_appointment",  "label": "Appointment page URL" },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Search — popular search chips"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Shown in the empty state of the search overlay (query typed so far is under 2 characters). Leave a label blank to hide that chip."
    },
    { "type": "text", "id": "search_chip_1_label", "label": "Chip 1 label", "default": "Signature" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "search_chip_1_url",   "label": "Chip 1 link",  "default": "/collections/bestsellers" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "search_chip_2_label", "label": "Chip 2 label", "default": "The Bloom Soirée" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "search_chip_2_url",   "label": "Chip 2 link",  "default": "/collections/the-bloom-soiree" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "search_chip_3_label", "label": "Chip 3 label", "default": "Chamakk" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "search_chip_3_url",   "label": "Chip 3 link",  "default": "/collections/chamak" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "search_chip_4_label", "label": "Chip 4 label", "default": "Barre Oblique" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "search_chip_4_url",   "label": "Chip 4 link",  "default": "/collections/barre-oblique" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "search_chip_5_label", "label": "Chip 5 label", "default": "The Festive Edit" },
    { "type": "url",  "id": "search_chip_5_url",   "label": "Chip 5 link",  "default": "/collections/the-festive-edit" },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Search — empty-state image tiles"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Three tiles shown below the popular-search chips. Leave an image blank to use the matching collection's existing card image as a launch-ready fallback (same fallback pattern as the Collection page's editorial insert)."
    },
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "search_tile_1_image",   "label": "Tile 1 image" },
    { "type": "text",         "id": "search_tile_1_caption", "label": "Tile 1 caption", "default": "The Bloom Soirée" },
    { "type": "url",          "id": "search_tile_1_url",     "label": "Tile 1 link",    "default": "/collections/the-bloom-soiree" },
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "search_tile_2_image",   "label": "Tile 2 image" },
    { "type": "text",         "id": "search_tile_2_caption", "label": "Tile 2 caption", "default": "Chamakk" },
    { "type": "url",          "id": "search_tile_2_url",     "label": "Tile 2 link",    "default": "/collections/chamak" },
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "search_tile_3_image",   "label": "Tile 3 image" },
    { "type": "text",         "id": "search_tile_3_caption", "label": "Tile 3 caption", "default": "Barre Oblique" },
    { "type": "url",          "id": "search_tile_3_url",     "label": "Tile 3 link",    "default": "/collections/barre-oblique" }
  ],
  "presets": [
    { "name": "Navigation" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}

